## This Week's Update for @nuance・23 

Today at 2/13/2024 1:00 PM we will release an update that affects both miners and validators. The update does not have huge impact on vtrust but should improve stability of vtrust over time.

When the new changes has been released, both validators and miners need to git pull and pm2 restart. Validators which run auto-updates will update automatically.
**New Changes: **
- We're starting the switch from SDXLTurbo to a better model, Realities Edge XL. We've reduced SDXLTurbo's incentive weight to 0.25 and assigned a 0.08 to the new model. SDXLTurbo will be phased out in 2 weeks.
 - We're also updating our user interface.
- Miner blacklisting is now based strictly on the amount of TAO staked:
  - Validator need at least 10,000 TAO staked.
  - Validators are limited to 10 requests to any specific miner every 10 minutes for every 10,000 TAO staked. Meaning that a validator with 100k can send 100 requests per 10 minutes to any single miner, so about 200 miner x 100 requests is 20 000 requests per ten minutes.
- Chances of getting rewards for organic requests are now 10%.
- Validators will now consider the last 10 rewards for each miner to set weight, up from 5 previously.

**Coming Soon:**
- We're introducing new features: Img2Img and ControlNet, expected by the end of February.

**Some stats**
- In the last 7 days the frontend was used to generate 2531 images. We will see this number rise as we add more functions and market the frontend.
- Three validators are participating as validator proxies. For any questions regarding validator proxies feel free to DM me.

- GitHub: https://github.com/NicheTensor/NicheImage


For anyone asking why their emissions are decreasing on their miners today, this could be from a few different reasons:
- Your miner is on a subnet that had its emissions decreased in order to spread them to the new subnets (Realistic Vision decreased by 4%)
- Your miner is running a model that had more miners move to that model. For example, if you're on Anime, I believe the % of miners went from about 28% to 31% while the emissions on Anime stayed the same at 34%, so the emissions per miner would have decreased slightly.
- You moved your miner to a new model and it's rebuilding incentive and history with the validators. This can take several hours which is why they paused registration for 15 hours.
